snippet: Planned Parenthood of New York City expects the new $9 million health center to open in Long Island City in 2015, and eventually serve 17,500 patients.
abstract: Planned Parenthood of New York City is poised to break ground on $9 million health center in Long Island City, Queens; expansion comes as parent organization suffers federal budget cuts and activist opposition to its abortion services across much of country.
lead_paragraph: Planned Parenthood of New York City expects the new $9 million health center to open in Long Island City in 2015, and eventually serve 17,500 patients.
